# EntropyNet - Claude Code Project Guide

## Project Overview

EntropyNet is a distributed protocol that guarantees data "forgetting" rather than persistence. It combines client-side secret sharing (Shamir's Secret Sharing) with volatile memory management on a P2P network (DHT).

## Tech Stack

- **Core**: Rust (entropynet-core) - crypto, protocol, in-memory store
- **Networking**: libp2p (entropynet-net) - TCP/QUIC, WebRTC/WebTransport
- **Browser SDK**: Wasm (entropynet-wasm) - JavaScript/TypeScript wrapper
- **Signaling**: WebSocket

